        "intro": "Portuguese verbs are divided into three conjugation groups based on their infinitive ending: -ar, -er, and -ir. Each group follows its own pattern of endings. Irregular verbs must be memorized individually. European Portuguese uses 5 person forms: eu, tu, ele/ela, nós, eles/elas.",
